    <h2 id="experience">Experience</h2>
    <h3>Who is SM?</h3>
    <p class="second">Seedhe Maut is a prominent Hindi hip-hop duo from New Delhi, India, comprising rapper-producer Calm (Siddhant Sharma) and rapper Encore ABJ (Abhijay Negi). Known for their aggressive and verbose lyrical style, they emerged from underground rap battles, releasing their debut album Bayaan in 2018, with the help of producer Sez on the Beat. They have since become major figures in the Indian hip-hop scene, known for their sharp rhymes and innovative approach to Hindi rap, and now run their own independent label, DL91.  </p>
    <h3>Key aspects of Seedhe Maut:</h3>
    <p class="third">Duo Members: Calm and Encore ABJ. 
Formation: Started in 2015, after meeting at a New Delhi rap battle series. 
Name Origin: The name comes from a slang term used by Calm's brother to describe something done with full potential. 
Musical Style: They are known for their hard-hitting, aggressive, and lyrical hip-hop with razor-sharp rhymes, and they push the boundaries of Hindi rap. 
Themes: Their music explores themes of urban youth, struggle, dreams, romance, politics, and society. 
Career Highlights:
Released their debut album Bayaan in 2018 via Azadi Records. 
Known for influential collaborations with artists like Ritviz, KR$NA, and MC Stan. 
Have a dedicated fanbase and are considered among the best rappers in India. 
Broke new ground with their first major UK tour without a major label's backing. 
Founded their own independent label, DL91, in 2024. 
Cultural Impact: They are seen as a force reevaluating youth culture in India and are a major part of the country's growing hip-hop subculture. </p>
